RESEARCH SUMMARY: MINDFUL WORK APP

METHODOLOGY:
Conducted a 10-question wellness survey across 10 diverse personas to identify stress triggers and relaxation preferences.

KEY FINDINGS:
1. The Privacy Gap: 80% of users avoid current wellness programs because they are "too public."
2. The Time Crunch: 7/10 employees can only spare 5-15 minutes for a break, necessitating "micro-sessions."
3. Sensory Variety: No single stimulus works for everyone. Technical staff prefer light/sound, while leadership roles prefer guided meditation/aroma.
4. Physical Impact: 60% of stress manifests as physical pain (headaches, eye strain, jaw clenching).

CONCLUSION:
The app must prioritize speed of access, complete privacy, and deep sensory customization via AI.
